According to WHO, there are more than 9,700 people infected in China and around 82 cases have been confirmed outside the country. CAPE TOWN - The World Health Organisation (WHO) has on Thursday declared the coronavirus outbreak an international public health emergency. According to WHO, there are more than 9,700 people infected in China and around 82 cases have been confirmed outside the country. Despite the disease spreading rapidly, WHO director general Tedros Ghebreyesus is impressed with Chinaâ€™s response. The organisation has issued technical advice to all member states as the outbreak shows no signs of slowing down, for now. It said all countries should be prepared for containment, active surveillance, early detection, isolation and management of cases.  